Over RCF roof $Stan Musial became the first player in major league history to hit five home runs in a doubleheader
$Vic Raschi struck below the right ankle and injured by Frank Baumholtz ball in first

$Wally Moon hit a low line drive; 3B umpire Hal Dixon ruled that Ralph Kiner had trapped the ball while 2B umpire Tom Gorman ruled a catch; Kiner threw the ball to 2B for the double play; Rip Repulski scored before the thrid out was made at 2B; Cardinals manager Eddie Stanky stomped and argued for 10 minutes and then protested the game
$Jim Willis was angry after Wally Moon's steal
$Red Schoendienst ran behind Tom Alston to take the roller and beat Joe Garagiola to the bag with a slide
$Tom Alston and Mel Wright collided on the popup in front of the mound

ej,riced101,P,gorea901,Bench jockeying Cardinal Rice, not in game, ejected by 2B umpire Gore for arguing that Musial was safe at 2nd because 2bman dropped ball; ruling was that ball was dropped during process of throwing to 1st after out was recorded

ej,stalg103,P,goetl901,Bench jockeying ej,stane101,M,goetl901,Called second strike $Wally Moon argued the called second strike; Cardinals manager Stanky trotted in from the 3B coach's box to talk to Moon; as he left, he made a comment to HP umpire Goetz and was ejected; Cardinals Staley ejected by Goetz from the bench
ej,poseb102,C,dascf901,Call at 1B Cardinals Coach Bill Posedel ejected by 1B umpire Frank Dascoli
$Alex Grammas unsuccessfully tried to bunt twice and was replaced
ej,repur101,P,conlj102,Interference call Rip Repluski called for interference and ejected by HP umpire Jocko Conlan
$Dee Fondy hit on mouth with throw in pre-game, suffered cut lip (internal) so Steve Bilko played 1B
$Gerry Staley left due to heat exhaustion
